-- PRESS DIGEST - Hong Kong - May 15
-- By Donny Kwok
-- Wed May 14, 2014 10:38PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 15 (Reuters) - These are some of the leading stories in Hong Kong newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST  -- The Hong Kong government issued an amber travel warning for Vietnam after protesters there vandalised hundreds of foreign-owned factories and torched at least 15 of them. (http://link.reuters.com/rev39v) -- Citic Pacific <0267.HK> has reached an agreement with 15 government funds and institutional investors to subscribe for HK$39.5 billion ($5.10 billion) of shares it will issue to finance the acquisition of its parent company's assets, in what is billed as a landmark deal that will help advance state enterprise reform on the mainland. (http://link.reuters.com/sev39v)  THE STANDARD -- Taiwanese merchants are scrambling to leave the Binh Duong industrial area in Vietnam after protesters torched several factories. They said when they drove to the airport vigilantes checked vehicles to see if there were mainlanders among the passengers. (http://link.reuters.com/buv39v) -- The Hong Kong home market regained momentum slightly following the adjustment of double stamp duty, as more homeowners seeking to buy better units flocked to make inquiries. (http://link.reuters.com/cuv39v)  HONG KONG ECONOMIC JOURNAL  -- Zhong An Real Estate <0672.HK> plans to spin off its commercial development and investment business unit, China New City, in a HK$2 billion ($258.00 million) global offering.APPLE DAILY -- Hong Kong's education minister urged teachers not to encourage students to participate in the unlawful Occupy Central movement, and reminded teachers of their legal responsibilities.